nd rollback-safe promotion steps.\n'@;\n'03-worker-health-check.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Worker Health Check\nInspect ops/runbooks/scripts for worker readiness. Identify missing scripts, broken path references, stale runbooks, and quick fixes. Return a ranked remediation checklist with estimated effort.\n'@;\n'04-job-pipeline-review.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Job Pipeline Review\nReview job_pipeline JSON + outputs/jobs artifacts. Summarize pipeline health, freshness, anomalies, and top 5 actions to improve throughput and reliability without destructive changes.\n'@;\n'05-mission-control-brief.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Mission Control Brief\nProduce a concise mission-control brief from current workspace state: wins, blockers, project statuses, worker statuses, and next 24-hour execution plan.\n'@;\n'06-linkedin-asset-packaging.md'=@'\n# Prompt: LinkedIn Asset Packaging\nFind and consolidate LinkedIn assets into reference/linkedin-assets using copy-first policy. Build an index by asset type (banner, cover, copy, contacts, templates) and propose publishing-ready packs.\n'@;\n'07-project-revival-sprint.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Project Revival Sprint\nCreate a 48-hour revival sprint for stalled projects (marketing-genius, replit-standalone, swing-analyzer, dinner-app). Include objective, deliverables, daily checkpoints, and clear owner tasks.\n'@;\n'08-drive-mirror-dedup.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Drive Mirror Dedup\nAnalyze duplication between top-level and projects/ folders in openclaw-workspace-main. Provide a deduplicated map, preferred canonical source per project, and safe sync policy.\n'@;\n'09-safe-background-ops.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Safe Background Ops\nRecommend scheduled background checks for inventory, worker health, and pipeline freshness. Include exact PowerShell and schtasks commands. No deletes or destructive sync.\n'@;\n'10-weekly-rebuild-retro.md'=@'\n# Prompt: Weekly Rebuild Retro\nRun a weekly retro on rebuild execution: what improved, what regressed, what stayed risky. Output KPI deltas, root causes, and prioritized actions for next week.\n'@\n}.GetEnumerator() | ForEach-Object { Set-Content -Path (Join-Path $base $_.Key) -Value $_.Value -Encoding UTF8 }\n","timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"$base='C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\prompts\\\\high-value';\\n@{\\n'01-canonical-audit.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Canonical Audit\\nAudit this workspace for canonical path drift. Focus on TonyOS, replit-standalone, replit-standalone-ui, marketing-genius, job_pipeline, swing-analyzer, dinner-app, linkedin-assets. Output: canonical path table, duplicate path table, and copy-first corrective actions only.\\n'@;\\n'02-recovery-staging-plan.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Recovery Staging Plan\\nDesign a non-destructive recovery staging plan using local workspace + G: mirrors. Include exact robocopy commands, staging directory layout, verification checks, and rollback-safe promotion steps.\\n'@;\\n'03-worker-health-check.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Worker Health Check\\nInspect ops/runbooks/scripts for worker readiness. Identify missing scripts, broken path references, stale runbooks, and quick fixes. Return a ranked remediation checklist with estimated effort.\\n'@;\\n'04-job-pipeline-review.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Job Pipeline Review\\nReview job_pipeline JSON + outputs/jobs artifacts. Summarize pipeline health, freshness, anomalies, and top 5 actions to improve throughput and reliability without destructive changes.\\n'@;\\n'05-mission-control-brief.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Mission Control Brief\\nProduce a concise mission-control brief from current workspace state: wins, blockers, project statuses, worker statuses, and next 24-hour execution plan.\\n'@;\\n'06-linkedin-asset-packaging.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: LinkedIn Asset Packaging\\nFind and consolidate LinkedIn assets into reference/linkedin-assets using copy-first policy. Build an index by asset type (banner, cover, copy, contacts, templates) and propose publishing-ready packs.\\n'@;\\n'07-project-revival-sprint.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Project Revival Sprint\\nCreate a 48-hour revival sprint for stalled projects (marketing-genius, replit-standalone, swing-analyzer, dinner-app). Include objective, deliverables, daily checkpoints, and clear owner tasks.\\n'@;\\n'08-drive-mirror-dedup.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Drive Mirror Dedup\\nAnalyze duplication between top-level and projects/ folders in openclaw-workspace-main. Provide a deduplicated map, preferred canonical source per project, and safe sync policy.\\n'@;\\n'09-safe-background-ops.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Safe Background Ops\\nRecommend scheduled background checks for inventory, worker health, and pipeline freshness. Include exact PowerShell and schtasks commands. No deletes or destructive sync.\\n'@;\\n'10-weekly-rebuild-retro.md'=@'\\n# Prompt: Weekly Rebuild Retro\\nRun a weekly retro on rebuild execution: what improved, what regressed, what stayed risky. Output KPI deltas, root causes, and prioritized actions for next week.\\n'@\\n}.GetEnumerator() | ForEach-Object { Set-Content -Path (Join-Path $base $_.Key) -Value $_.Value -Encoding UTF8 }\\n\",\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":189,"output":708,"cacheRead":32256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33153,"cost":{"input":0.00033075,"output":0.009912,"cacheRead":0.0056448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01588755}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773082912363}}
