openclaw-full-main` appears to be full OpenClaw system-state mirror, not a clean project mirror.\n- Several local canonical project folders exist but are currently stubs/near-empty.\n- LinkedIn assets are mostly in archive TonyOS paths + Drive `linkedin-background`.\n\n---\n\n### 2) Canonical project/worker/workflow map built (deduplicated policy)\nCreated canonical mapping for:\n- TonyOS\n- replit-standalone\n- replit-standalone-ui\n- marketing-genius\n- job pipeline\n- swing-analyzer\n- dinner-app\n- linkedin assets\n\nCanonical root policy set to local workspace (`C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace`) with copy-first recovery sources from Drive/archives.\n\n---\n\n### 3) Requested files produced\n\n**In `workspace/ops`:**\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\ops\\FULL_INVENTORY_REPORT.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\ops\\PROJECT_CANONICAL_MAP.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\ops\\TASK_BACKLOG_PRIORITIZED.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\ops\\SAFE_BACKGROUND_EXECUTION_SCHEDULE.md` *(added for item #5)*\n\n**In `workspace/runbooks`:**\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\runbooks\\WORKER_RECOVERY_PLAN.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\runbooks\\WORKFLOW_BLUEPRINT_V1.md`\n\n---\n\n### 4) Prompt/task library refreshed (10 high-value prompts)\n- Index:\n  - `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\prompts\\TOP_10_HIGH_VALUE_PROMPTS_TONY.md`\n- Prompt files:\n  - `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\prompts\\high-value\\01-canonical-audit.md`\n  - `...\\02-recovery-staging-plan.md`\n  - `...\\03-worker-health-check.md`\n  - `...\\04-job-pipeline-review.md`\n  - `...\\05-mission-control-brief.md`\n  - `...\\06-linkedin-asset-packaging.md`\n  - `...\\07-project-revival-sprint.md`\n  - `...\\08-drive-mirror-dedup.md`\n  - `...\\09-safe-background-ops.md`\n  - `...\\10-weekly-rebuild-retro.md`\n\n---\n\n### 5) Safe background execution schedule recommendation with exact commands\nIncluded in:\n- `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace\\ops\\SAFE_BACKGROUND_EXECUTION_SCHEDULE.md`\n\nContains exact `schtasks` commands and safe-copy examples (`robocopy` without destructive flags).\n\n---\n\n### 6) Safety compliance\n- No deletions performed.\n- No destructive sync/mirror operations performed.\n- All recommendations are copy-first.\n\n## Top priorities (next actions)\n1. Run **Stage 1–3** from `runbooks/WORKER_RECOVERY_PLAN.md` to hydrate stub projects from mirror into staging, then promote copy-only.\n2. Finalize canonical naming decision for `swing-analysis` vs `swing-analyzer`.\n3. Populate `reference/linkedin-assets` from Drive + archived TonyOS LinkedIn files.\n4. Activate safe scheduled checks from `ops/SAFE_BACKGROUND_EXECUTION_SCHEDULE.md`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ee0a16fa10bd7250169af195bfe78819399cf79365065d7a1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":1182,"output":871,"cacheRead":33280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35333,"cost":{"input":0.0020685,"output":0.012194,"cacheRead":0.005823999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0200865}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773082968798}}
